# Finance Data Isolation

This plan details the implementation of strict data isolation for the Finance module, ensuring that Store Admins only see financial data belonging to their active store, and establishing a robust schema for financial transactions.

## Open Questions
> [!WARNING]
> Currently, expenses and vendor payouts are calculated dynamically as a percentage of total revenue (`opex = totalRevenue * 0.11`). Should I create formal database schemas for **Expenses** and **Vendor Payments** so they can be logged individually, or should I continue calculating them proportionally but strictly isolated by store?

## Proposed Changes

### Database Security
#### [MODIFY] [firestore.rules](file:///c:/Users/praga/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/jewellery-website/firestore.rules)
- Add security rules for a new `transactions` collection.
- Ensure `allow read, write: if isStaffOrHigher() && isAssignedToStore(resource.data.storeId)`.

### Hooks
#### [NEW] [useFinance.js](file:///c:/Users/praga/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/jewellery-website/src/hooks/useFinance.js)
- Create a dedicated hook to manage isolated financial data.
- Fetch from `transactions` collection using `getStoreQuery(db, 'transactions', activeStoreId)`.
- Expose distinct methods for: `addRevenue`, `addExpense`, `recordTax`, and `recordVendorPayment`.
- Ensure all created transactions strictly enforce `storeId: activeStoreId`.

#### [MODIFY] [useOrders.js](file:///c:/Users/praga/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/jewellery-website/src/hooks/useOrders.js)
